- When running in development mode
  - Since cas authentication should redirect back to our website, please use public hostname instead of localhost. (even for browsing)
    Hostname can be configured with the following node command
      - require('os').hostname()
  - Ports configuration
    - To run client on port XX, modify followings
      - client/.env --> PORT=XX
      - server/index.js --> res.header("Access-Control-Allow-Origin", "https://[hostnamme]:XX"); (This is to enable cors)
    - To run server on port YY, modify followings
      - client/src/config.js --> module.exports.server = 'https://[server_hostname]:YY'
      - server/index.js --> console.log("\n\n[Server] Starting server on port YY")
      - server/index.js --> .listen(YY, '0.0.0.0')


- Extras
    - Enable service worker for performance(but only on deployment)